[AGENT: BUDGET]

Dining is often the fastest category to trim without touching fixed bills, because it is mostly habit-driven. If you set a weekly cap and plan groceries, you usually see progress within two weeks without feeling deprived.

{"intent":"budget_plan","steps":["Review last 30 days dining transactions","Set a weekly dining cap","Track against the cap weekly"],"tools_needed":["list_transactions","set_budget"],"notes":"focus=dining"}

[AGENT: INVESTMENT]

Single-stock concentration can dominate risk even when the company is strong; your horizon and cushion matter more than the ticker story. Start by sizing the position against your total portfolio and your ability to hold through drawdowns.

{"intent":"investment_analysis","steps":["Fetch AAPL quote and recent history","Summarize volatility and trend","Compare to your overall equity exposure"],"tools_needed":["market_quote"],"notes":"symbol=AAPL"}

[AGENT: INVOICE]

Clients pay faster when each line has a plain-English description, quantity, rate, and line total—then a single grand total. If tax applies, show it as a separate line rather than burying it in rounding.

{"intent":"invoice","steps":["List line items with amounts","Add subtotal and taxes if applicable","Export PDF and store invoice id"],"tools_needed":["generate_invoice"],"notes":"type=consulting"}
